Content-Description: Security_PolicyFactory updates and 'any' operators for locals (fwd)

Date: Fri, 1 Feb 2002 14:49:24 -0600 (CST)
From: Chris Cleeland <cleeland@ociweb.com>
To: Ossama Othman <ossama@ece.uci.edu>,  <parsons@cs.wustl.edu>
cc: Tom Venturella <venturella_t@ociweb.com>
Subject: Security_PolicyFactory updates and 'any' operators for locals
Message-ID: <Pine.LNX.4.33.0202011443420.25560-100000@ocilap5.ociweb.com>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; charset=US-ASCII


Hi, Ossama & Jeff,

Tom's in the middle of trying to test some stuff out using some of the
concocted examples Ossama sent awhile back.  In one case it shows the
following snippet of code:

  SecurityLevel2::CredentialsList creds_list;
  ...
  CORBA::Any clany;
  clany <<= creds_list;

This fails because the IDL compiler didn't generate any insertion operators
for CredentialsList.  Here's the salient information on Credentials and
CredentialsList:

  local interface Credentials { .... };
  typedef sequence<Credentials> CredentialsList;

Seems that the IDL compiler doesn't generate 'any' insertion operators for a
local interface.  I've tried to find documentation to that effect in a spec
somewhere, but haven't been able to locate it.  Can that be right?!

Also, Ossama, we noticed that the Security_PolicyFactory::create_policy
doesn't seem to do anything at all with the SecInvocationsCredentialsPolicy.
I presume that's an oversight and I'm happy to fix that, but is it really as
simple as mimicking the code that's in there for the other policies?

Thanks!
-cj

-- 
  Chris Cleeland, cleeland_c @ ociweb.com, http://www.milodesigns.com/~chris
