Content-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; charset=US-ASCII


On Fri, 1 Feb 2002, Ossama Othman wrote:

> Hi Jeff,
>
> On Fri, Feb 01, 2002 at 09:01:49PM -0600, Jeff Parsons wrote:
> > In the case where a local interface is marshaled inside an Any, I don't
> > think
> > it would be too bad -- we could check the typecode inside the Any <<
> > operator.
> > Not sure about the case where we marshal a bare local interface though. How
> > do you tell whether you're using the CDR operator to marshal it or to put it
> > into an Any?
>
> The CCM spec seems to imply that attempting to insert a locality
> constrained interface into Any is illegal.  I'm not sure if this is
> too restrictive, but it seems like we're out of luck in any case.

No, I interpret it differently.  What the spec is saying (and, btw, the 2.4.2
spec had the same thing in it that you put in, Ossama) is that, if you try to
marshal an any which contains a local interface, then you're out of luck.

If you accept that interpretation, then it should be okay to insert a local
interface into an any; just don't try to pass it across the wire.

-- 
