Hi Chris,

On Fri, Feb 01, 2002 at 11:52:26PM -0600, Chris Cleeland wrote:
> <yoda>like YOUR interpretation better, do I.  More useful...it is!</yoda>

Strong is the force with you Master Yoda.  :-)

> Yes.  I'm not sure what to do about the CDR thing, Jeff.  I started hacking
> on the IDL compiler and ran into that this evening.  Seems that what we'd
> have to do is somehow mark the CDR stream as "blessed" to hold a local.  If
> we mark the stream, we'll also be able to easily detect that an any is
> holding a local without interpreting the type.
> 
> Would that work?  Or is there a better way to solve this problem?

Couldn't we just add another Any::_tao_replace() method that only
accepts a TypeCode and the value?  That method wouldn't instantiate a
message block as the existing code does.  The IDL compiler would
only need to generate the Any insertion/extraction operators that
set/get value and compare the TypeCodes when appropriate.  No need
for the CDR stream insertion/extraction operators.

Of course, I haven't looked into how this would be implemented so I
may be entirely off base here.

-Ossama
-- 
Ossama Othman <ossama@ece.uci.edu>
