On Sat, 2 Feb 2002, Ossama Othman wrote:

> Couldn't we just add another Any::_tao_replace() method that only
> accepts a TypeCode and the value?  That method wouldn't instantiate a
> message block as the existing code does.  The IDL compiler would
> only need to generate the Any insertion/extraction operators that
> set/get value and compare the TypeCodes when appropriate.  No need
> for the CDR stream insertion/extraction operators.

Hey, that's a good point.  I could just make a C++ copy of the object.  So
the any insertion operators would be implemented differently, and the any
would just hold a copy of the object.  It would be pretty easy to catch
marshalling and stop it in that case since there'd be no message block or cdr
stream to manipulate, eh?

> Of course, I haven't looked into how this would be implemented so I may
> be entirely off base here.

Let's hope not!  Jeff whaddya think?

I will now formally ask, Jeff, that if you undertake this that you insure
that it's not boudn up with other pending changes so that we can integrate it
back into our release more easily.

Thanks!
-cj

PS  Should I enter a bugzilla bug for this?  You want me to record all our
conversation on the topic?

