Hi,

>The implementation would still inherit from CORBA::LocalObject.  That
>would prevent object_to_string() from working, but I'm not sure about
>the CDR stream insertion operator.


Maybe I missed something about the security implementation, but FYI,
the IDL compiler generates local interfaces as inheriting from
CORBA::Object. As I understand it, if the user wants things like
reference counting, she can mixin TAO_Local_Refcounted_Object, which
inherits from CORBA::LocalObject.

Jeff

