Hi Chris,

On Fri, Feb 01, 2002 at 03:28:01PM -0600, Chris Cleeland wrote:
> Besides, it had just come out, and I doubted that Jeff would've had time to
> digest the whole thing.  If 2.4.2 (which has been out for awhile) permitted
> insertion of a local into an 'any' then I thought I had some ammunition.

The CORBA spec doesn't deal with the "local" keyword yet.  It just
mentions "locality constrained" interfaces.  The stuff we want is
dealt with in the CCM / CORBA 3.0 spec.  Here's what I found in
section 3.8.6.1 of that document (ptc/99-10-03  ---  is there a more
recent version?):

-----
Local types cannot be marshaled and references to local objects cannot
be converted to strings. Any attempt to marshal a local object, such
as via an unconstrained base interface, as an Object, or as the
contents of an any, or to pass a local object to
ORB::object_to_string, shall result in a MARSHAL system exception with
OMG minor code 2.
-----

Looks like we're out of luck!  I'll run through the Security spec
again.  I must have missed something.  This is annoying.

> You don't know Jeff's ph# by any chance, do you?

Nope.

-Ossama
